2026-03-28T06:28:38.6633549Z               "id": "1049c6b29d28ee104875cf58ab3f436b1642ffea",
2026-03-28T06:28:38.6640396Z               "message": "Fall back to individual sends when batch email delivery fails\n\nWhen SES rejects a multi-recipient send (e.g. one invalid or unverified\naddress), the whole batch silently fails. This change catches the batch\nfailure and retries each address individually, appending a footer note to\nthe email explaining why it was sent individually.\n\n- EmailRenderer.AppendFallbackNote inserts a styled note before the\n  closing HTML tag\n- EmailSchedulerService.SendCustomerEmailAsync catches batch failures,\n  skips fallback for single recipients, sends individually to all\n  To+CC+BCC addresses, re-throws only if every individual send also fails\n- OperationCanceledException propagates immediately without triggering\n  fallback\n- 11 new tests covering all branches: batch success, single-recipient\n  no-fallback, To+CC+BCC combined, cancellation, all-fail rethrow,\n  partial success, and fallback HTML content\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01GYPAPQwDpWkpzVSP1ync2h",
